.TH AMLABEL 8
.SH NAME
amlabel \- labels an Amanda tape
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B amlabel
.I config label [
.B slot
.I number ]

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B Amlabel
writes an Amanda label on the tape in the tape drive specified by the
.I amanda.conf
file in @CONFIG_DIR@/\fIconfig\fR.  The
.I label
can be any string that does not contain whitespace, and that matches the
.I amanda.conf 
.B labelstr
regular expression parameter.  It is up to the
system administrators to define a naming convention.

An optional slot number may be specified after the tape label.  If a
tape changer is in use, amlabel will label the tape in the specified
slot, instead of labeling the currently loaded tape.

See the
.IR amanda(8)
man page for more details about Amanda.

.SH EXAMPLE
.TP
% amlabel @DEFAULT_CONFIG@ VOL1
If the line "tapedev /dev/tape/1n" is in
@CONFIG_DIR@/@DEFAULT_CONFIG@/amanda.conf, an Amanda label with the name "VOL1" is
written on the /dev/tape/1n device.

.TP
% amlabel @DEFAULT_CONFIG@ VOL2 slot 3
Labels the tape in slot 3 of the currently configured tape changer.

